	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=187394><span id= >Ulvian</span></a><br><span id=notbold>216 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.37]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>No, Rangers would not want this weapon most likely, and let me tell you why.<br><br>Seeing as warriors become dependant on pure aggro proccing weapons around the higher end of the game (Hategiver, Blade of Carnage) those are the weapons they get.<br><br>Bards get weapons which have instrument skills, and innately high damage/delay ratios to compensate for their low offensive skills to some extent.<br><br>Paladins and Shadowknights rely on &quot;Class&quot; One hand slash, two hand slash, etc weapons which also have innately high damage/delay ratios.<br><br>Rangers who are in a guild capable of taking this mob out, are more than likely either already wielding,or soon to be wielding Acrylia Handled Broadsword + Vhyz`Dra's Render of Souls combo.<br><br>And as it stands, the Acrylia Handled is superior to this weapon for a ranger seeing as our piercing only caps at 240 skill or so. Therefore we do less damage with a 16/19 piercer than we would do with a 16/19 one hand slasher.<br><br>Its true that this weapon has nice added stats also, but don't forget what you said yourself, Rangers are a damage class, and as such damage/delay and damage capabilities of weapons are our priorities, much moreso than stats a weapon carries.<br><br>Im sure all Rangers would agree that if the choice came between AHB (16/19 with stats) and lets say a new weapon, with the stats of 17/18 and 0 stats whatsoever, the AHB would get bagged.<br><br>This Dagger belongs in the hands of a rogue, seeing as 16 damage is currently the highest availeable to them, and the 1 fire damage modifier makes this weapon potentially a 17 damage piercer, highest and best out there at current time. Maybe better will become availeable in the same tier as this weapon, but we will have to wait and see.<br><br>As it stands, this might as well be re-named to Ragebringer 2.0 (AKA: Rogue weapon)</p>&nbsp;<br>Ulvian Stormweaver<br>Warder of Veeshan<br>-Rage above the storm-</td></td></tr>
